# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare Pages equivalent of the [[redirects]] tree in netlify.toml.
# Docusaurus copies static/ to the build root, where Cloudflare Pages parses
# this file and applies the rules to asset responses.
#
# IMPORTANT - trailing slashes:
#   Cloudflare matches the source path EXACTLY, including the trailing slash
#   (Netlify matched both forms). To preserve the old behavior, every rule is
#   listed in BOTH slash forms (`/x` and `/x/`), and each splat rule also gets
#   a bare-path entry so `/prefix` (no slash) redirects like `/prefix/...`.
#
#   All rules are 301. Static rules precede the splat rules at the bottom.
#
# NOT INCLUDED - the cross-domain developer.helium.com rules from netlify.toml.
#   `_redirects` matches on path, not host, so recreate those as a zone-level
#   Redirect Rule in the Cloudflare dashboard.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

